        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 13 at 2:20PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>At 219 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Collbran, or 34 miles east of Grand Junction, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Collbran and Plateau City.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
